ctMachine()`. This is a backend API call that starts/resumes the computer. We don't build this in PR 1, but the hook's structure accommodates it -- just add a new case in the strategy selection.\n\n### Scope of PR 1\n\n**In scope:**\n- `useComputerPreconnection` hook + tests\n- Integration into `NewSession.module.tsx` (trigger on computer selection)\n- Provider-specific error messages (BYOM vs E2B)\n- UI state in `ComputerSelector.view.tsx`: connection indicator (connecting/connected/failed) and retry button\n- Clean disconnect on computer change / deselect / unmount\n\n**Out of scope (PR 2):**\n- Working directory validation via preconnected client\n- Recent directories fetching (new daemon method needed)\n- `WorkingDirectorySection` component\n- MCP OAuth relay changes (separate concern, should be its own PR)\n\n### Files to create/modify\n\n1. **New**: `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/hooks/useComputerPreconnection.ts`\n2. **New**: `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/hooks/useComputerPreconnection.test.ts`\n3. **Modify**: `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/modules/NewSession.module.tsx` -- call the hook, pass state down\n4. **Modify**: `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/components/ComputerSelector.view.tsx` -- display connection state indicator\n5. **Possibly modify**: `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/services/types.ts` -- if we need new types for the preconnection props\n\n### Addressing PR review feedback\n\n- **Grouped props**: Connection state will be passed as a single `preconnection: PreconnectionState` prop, not scattered individual optional props\n- **Stronger types**: Discriminated union `PreconnectionState` eliminates impossible states\n- **React-safe side effects**: Connection logic in `useEffect` with proper cleanup/abort, not in render phase\n- **Stale closure prevention**: `useEffect` cleanup cancels in-flight connections before starting new ones\n\n---\n\n## PR 2: Working Directory Components (depends on PR 1)\n\n##