            "plan": "\n## Revision Summary\n\n- **Connection URL**: `computer.relayClientUrl ?? wss://${computer.hostname}`, matching current `NewSession.module.tsx` behavior. Fail-fast only when both are absent (computer not provisioned).\n- **No auto-restart**: Both BYOM and E2B use the same `connectMachine` polling path. No restart logic.\n- **Enum for status**: `PreconnectionStatus` in `packages/common/src/shared/enums.ts`.\n\n---\n\n## Types\n\n```typescript\n// packages/common/src/shared/enums.ts\nenum PreconnectionStatus {\n  Idle = 'idle',\n  Connecting = 'connecting',\n  Connected = 'connected',\n  Failed = 'failed',\n}\n```\n\n```typescript\n// In the hook file\ninterface RecoveryGuidance {\n  providerType: ComputerProviderType;\n  message: string;\n}\n\ntype PreconnectionState =\n  | { status: PreconnectionStatus.Idle }\n  | { status: PreconnectionStatus.Connecting; computerId: string }\n  | { status: PreconnectionStatus.Connected; computerId: string; client: DaemonSessionController }\n  | { status: PreconnectionStatus.Failed; computerId: string; error: string; recovery: RecoveryGuidance };\n\ninterface UseComputerPreconnectionProps {\n  computer: Computer | null;\n  enabled: boolean;\n}\n\ninterface UseComputerPreconnectionResult {\n  state: PreconnectionState;\n  retry: () => void;\n}\n```\n\n**URL resolution** (internal to hook):\n```typescript\nfunction getComputerWsUrl(computer: Computer): string | null {\n  if (computer.relayClientUrl) return computer.relayClientUrl;\n  if (computer.hostname) return `wss://${computer.hostname}`;\n  return null; // not provisioned\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Test Suite: `useComputerPreconnection.test.ts`\n\n### Mock Setup\n\n```typescript\nconst mocks = {\n  droidConnectionManager: {\n    connectMachine: vi.fn(),\n    disconnectMachine: vi.fn(),\n    removeMachine: vi.fn(),\n    hasMachine: vi.fn(),\n  },\n};\n```\n\nTest fixtures for 4 computer variants:\n- `byomComputer` -- has `relayClientUrl`, no `hostname`, provider `Byom`\n- `e2bRelayComputer` -- has both `relayClientUrl` and `hostname`, provider `E2b`\n- `e2bDirectComputer` -- has `hostname` only (no relay), provider `E2b`\n- `unprovisionedComputer` -- has neither `relayClientUrl` nor `hostname`\n\n---\n\n### Tests (19 total)\n\n#### Idle state (3)\n1. **returns idle when computer is null** -- `status === Idle`, `connectMachine` not called\n2. **returns idle when enabled is false** -- same\n3. **returns idle when disabled even with computer selected** -- same\n\n#### Successful connection (4)\n4. **connects BYOM computer via relayClientUrl** -- `connectMachine('byom-1', { type: Computer, url: relayClientUrl })`, transitions `Connecting → Connected`\n5. **connects E2B computer via relayClientUrl when available** -- uses `relayClientUrl` (not hostname)\n6. **connects E2B computer via hostname when no relayClientUrl** -- falls back to `wss://${hostname}`\n7. **exposes client in connected state** -- `state.client` is the resolved `DaemonSessionController`\n\n#### Failed connection (4)\n8. **transitions to failed when connectMachine rejects** -- `status === Failed`, `error` set\n9. **provides BYOM recovery guidance on failure** -- `recovery.providerType === Byom`, message re: daemon\n10. **provides E2B recovery guidance on failure** -- `recovery.providerType === E2b`, message re: computer\n11. **fails immediately when computer has no hostname and no relayClientUrl** -- `status === Failed`, `connectMachine` not called, error mentions provisioning\n\n#### Computer selection changes (3)\n12. **disconnects previous and connects new when selection changes** -- `disconnectMachine(old)` + `removeMachine(old)` then `connectMachine(new, ...)`\n13. **resets to connecting for new computer** -- `status === Connecting, computerId === newId`\n14. **cleans up and returns idle when computer deselected** -- cleanup on previous, `status === Idle`\n\n#### Stale connection / abort (2)\n15. **ignores stale resolve after computer changed** -- old promise