            "plan": "\n## Working Directory Validation for Computer Sessions\n\n### Goal\nOnce a computer is preconnected, validate the working directory and show recent directories — reusing the daemon connection established by `useComputerPreconnection`. This is PR 2 of the split from the original PR #10783.\n\n### Design Principles Assessment\n- **Pull complexity downward**: The `WorkingDirectorySection` component hides recent directory scrolling/selection logic from callers. The validation logic is centralized in `NewSession.module.tsx` rather than scattered.\n- **Information hiding**: `ComputerSelectorView` doesn't know about connection managers or daemon clients — it receives ready-to-display props.\n- **Deep module**: `WorkingDirectorySection` replaces `WorkingDirectoryInput` + inline recent directories in both `LocalMachineConfig` and `ComputerSelectorView`, consolidating ~80 lines of duplicated UI into one reusable component.\n\n### Changes\n\n#### 1. New: `WorkingDirectorySection` component (component-library)\nExtracted from the original PR verbatim. Combines `WorkingDirectoryInput` with optional recent directories list, validation error display, and scroll handling.\n\n**Files:**\n- `packages/component-library/src/settings/WorkingDirectorySection/WorkingDirectorySection.tsx` (new, ~141 lines)\n- `packages/component-library/src/settings/WorkingDirectorySection/WorkingDirectorySection.test.tsx` (new)\n- `packages/component-library/src/settings/WorkingDirectorySection/WorkingDirectorySection.stories.tsx` (new)\n- `packages/component-library/src/index.ts` — export `WorkingDirectorySection`\n\n#### 2. Refactor: `LocalMachineConfig` uses `WorkingDirectorySection`\nReplace the inline `WorkingDirectoryInput` + recent directories list with `WorkingDirectorySection`. This removes ~70 lines of duplicated styled-component code and the `StyledDirectoryItem`.\n\n**File:** `packages/component-library/src/settings/LocalMachineConfig/LocalMachineConfig.tsx`\n\n#### 3. Update: `ComputerSelectorView` uses `WorkingDirectorySection`\nReplace `WorkingDirectoryInput` with `WorkingDirectorySection`, adding new props for validation state and recent directories. These are only shown when the preconnection is `Connected`.\n\n**New props on `ComputerSelectorViewProps`:**\n```typescript\nisValidatingCwd?: boolean;\nvalidationError?: string;\nrecentDirectories?: string[];\nselectedDirectory?: string;\nonDirectorySelect?: (dir: string) => void;\n```\n\nThese get grouped with the existing `preconnection` prop flow (all gated on connection being established).\n\n#### 4. Update: `MachineConfigurationModal` — pass through new props\nAdd `isValidatingCwd`, `validationError`, `recentDirectories`, `selectedDirectory`, `onDirectorySelect` to the `ComputerSelectorViewProps` interface and `MachineConfigurationModalProps`, and pass them through.\n\n#### 5. Update: `NewSession.module.tsx` — validation + recent directories for computers\n\n**Key logic (adapted from original PR #10783):**\n\n- **`RecentDirectoriesFetcher`**: Generalize to accept a `machineId` prop instead of hardcoding `LOCAL_MACHINE_ID`. Render with `key={machineId}` so it re-fetches when the connected machine changes. Gate on preconnection being `Connected`.\n\n- **CWD validation**: The existing `handleCwdValidation` already uses `droidConnectionManager.getDaemonConnection(machineId)`. We extend it to work with the computer's machine ID when the computer tab is active and connected. Use a `lastValidatedCwdKey` ref (`machineType:machineId:cwd`) to avoid re-validating the same directory.\n\n- **Auto-validate on connect**: When `preconnection.state.status` transitions to `Connected`, trigger validation if there's a `selectedWorkingDirectory`. Uses the validation key to prevent duplicate calls.\n\n- **Default working directory**: When a computer is selected and has no persisted cwd, set a default: `~` for BYOM, `/home/factory` for E2B.\n\n- **Clear validation on cwd change**: Reset `cwdValidationError` and `lastValidatedCwdKey` when the user changes the working directory or selects a different computer.\n\n- **Confirm button gating**: Disable the Confirm button on the Computer tab until `preconnection.status === Connected` AND `isCwdValid` AND `selectedWorkingDirectory` is set.\n\n- **Status bar sentences**: Update the computer status sentences in the new-session header to show validation errors and connecting state (matching the original PR's approach).\n\n#### 6. Update: `ComputerSelector.view.test.tsx`\nAdd tests for validation error display and recent directories rendering.\n\n### What we're NOT doing (scope boundary)\n- **No auto-restart**: The original PR had `useMutateRestartComputer` for E2B machines. This doesn't exist yet and adds backend lifecycle complexity. We skip it — failed connections show the retry button from PR 1.\n- **No MCP OAuth relay changes**: Those are unrelated to working directory validation.\n- **No `StartingMachine` connection state**: We use `PreconnectionStatus` (Idle/Connecting/Connected/Failed), not `ConnectionState`. No new states needed.\n\n### Test plan\n- Existing 21 hook tests + 7 view tests continue passing\n- New `WorkingDirectorySection` tests (from original PR)\n- Updated `ComputerSelector.view.test.tsx` tests for validation UI\n- Typecheck, lint, knip across `@factory/common`, `@factory/frontend`, `@factory/component-library`\n",
